parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbo charge pipe can cause a sudden loss of engine power, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
Hydrolocking the engine can cause significant damage to the engine, leading to costly repairs or even engine replacement, and potentially causing accidents due to loss of vehicle control.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at low speeds or in confined spaces.
The failure of the charge pipe can cause a loss of power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: visible signs of broken or damaged pipes under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, shut off, or lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The stalling of the engine can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs on a busy road or highway.
The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially in hazardous weather conditions.
symptoms: a "Drive Train Malfunction" warning message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle is unable to be driven and needs to be towed
the fuel pump assembly needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel tank leak can cause a strong odor of gas, which can lead to safety and emissions issues, and potentially cause accidents or fires.
symptoms: A strong odor of gas is present
especially when the gas tank is full
the fuel pressure sending unit is faulty
the fuel tank needs to be replaced.
